DISCOVERING DEVICES CONNECTED TO THE SAME NETWORK 
=================================================

note:
remember to return your interface to managed mode 

INFORMATION GATHERING:
- discover all devices
- display their:
a. ip address
b. mac address 
c. operating system 
d. open ports 
e. running services 
f. etc...

- there are a number of programs that will do this:
a. net discover 
b. NMap 

NET DISCOVER
------------

> netdiscover -r 192.168.1.1/254

note:
-r --> this is an ip range to search for 

the first ip:
192.168.1.0
the last ip:
192.168.1.254

- 254 is the last ip a client can have 

